{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Reusable SwiftUI calendar records UI for apps that own their own data, persistence, and navigation."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/recordscalendarui"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI"},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarUI"},{"type":"text","text":" provides presentation-only calendar components for record-based apps. Host apps pass records, display configuration, selection state, and callbacks while keeping storage and detail navigation outside the package."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this package when you need a reusable week\/month calendar with a selected-day list and swipe-to-delete behavior, but each app needs different record values, text formatting, and detail screens."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Week scope uses the display calendar’s locale and first weekday to create a localized year, month, and week-of-month header. A Korean calendar displays a title such as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"2026년 7월 1주차"},{"type":"text","text":" without host formatting, and the week number follows the visible calendar grid."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Built-in week-title localizations cover English, Simplified Chinese, Traditional Chinese, French, German, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Portuguese (Portugal), and Spanish. Other locales fall back to English."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration.rowHeight"},{"type":"text","text":" controls the minimum selected-day row card height. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration.rowSpacing"},{"type":"text","text":" controls the vertical spacing between selected-day rows, defaults to 5 points, can be customized by host apps, and clamps negative values to zero. Values below "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration<YourRecord>.minimumRowHeight"},{"type":"text","text":", currently 44 points, are clamped so row content keeps a standard touch target. Row spacing does not reduce the configured row height. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration<YourRecord>.minimumRowHeight(forRowSpacing:)"},{"type":"text","text":" remains as a deprecated compatibility helper; use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"minimumRowHeight"},{"type":"text","text":" for new code."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration.theme"},{"type":"text","text":" accepts semantic colors through "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarTheme"},{"type":"text","text":", including the full-page background, calendar and record container background, primary and secondary page content colors, optional container-only primary and secondary content colors, and independent light and dark summary tile backgrounds. The default "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".standard"},{"type":"text","text":" theme preserves the system grouped page background, material calendar container, grouped record containers, and existing green appearance. Host apps can supply adaptive SwiftUI colors without changing package internals."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Theme initialization without an explicit light-mode secondary content color remains supported and derives that color from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"contentColor"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To change only surfaces, copy "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".standard"},{"type":"text","text":" and set "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"backgroundColor"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"containerBackgroundColor"},{"type":"text","text":". The package applies the container color consistently to the calendar, selected-day empty state, and record rows. Set "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"containerContentColor"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"containerSecondaryContentColor"},{"type":"text","text":" when those containers need a foreground palette that differs from the page. Selected calendar days continue to use the page primary content color so it remains paired with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"selectedDayBackgroundColor"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Calendar day buttons can receive an accessibility label and value from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":". The package passes a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarDayAccessibilityContext"},{"type":"text","text":" with the date, its display calendar, and the today, selected, and has-records states so host apps can provide their own localized full-date label and state text. Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context.calendar"},{"type":"text","text":" when formatting the date so its locale and time zone stay consistent with the visible calendar. When these closures are omitted, the package preserves SwiftUI’s default day-number announcement. Selected dates also use the system selected accessibility trait."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarView","doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarConfiguration","doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarWeekTitleContext","doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarTheme","doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarDisplayScope"],"title":"Calendar Presentation","anchor":"Calendar-Presentation"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarEntry"],"title":"Record Model Boundary","anchor":"Record-Model-Boundary"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarBestValueComparator","doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarDayAccessibilityContext"],"title":"Structures","anchor":"Structures"}],"metadata":{"title":"RecordsCalendarUI","roleHeading":"Framework","modules":[{"name":"RecordsCalendarUI"}],"role":"collection","symbolKind":"module","externalID":"RecordsCalendarUI"},"references":{"doc://recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI/documentation/RecordsCalendarUI/RecordsCalendarTheme":{"url":"\/documentation\/recordscalendarui\/recordscalendartheme","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"RecordsCalendarTheme"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarTheme","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"RecordsCalendarTheme"}],"title":"RecordsCalendarTheme"},"doc://recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI/documentation/RecordsCalendarUI/RecordsCalendarBestValueComparator":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarBestValueComparator","url":"\/documentation\/recordscalendarui\/recordscalendarbestvaluecomparator","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"RecordsCalendarBestValueComparator","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"RecordsCalendarBestValueComparator","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text"